reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value, quiet fan
reviews.reviewText: Great price on a good set of fans. The hub system makes it easy to use in lots of different projects. You can use the remote or connect it to a PC to change the colors and patterns of the lights.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cheap but Decent
reviews.reviewText: In electronics you get what you pay for. However, given the price of these, I’m not disappointed at all. Good value fans for someone on a budget. Bought them because I was too lazy to clean my old ones and didn’t want to pay the extortion-level fees of a Corsair. Worth the money if your primary goal is moving air through your system efficiently.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars These fans cannot be beat for the price!
reviews.reviewText: These fans cannot be beat for the price. They provide more than adequate cooling, and look great. My only minor complaints are that the lighting is very centralized, it doesn’t diffuse to cover the fan blades well. They also cause slight vibration of my case/desk at high speeds, though the cooling they offer at lower speeds is plenty for my 4070. Finally they will sometimes switch color profiles randomly, though this could be caused by one of my neighbors using an RGB/LED controller.Overall I would absolutely suggest this product, it is a great budget set of RGB case fans with minor issues.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2022
reviews.reviewText: These Fans are amazing, the rbg is bright and the colors looks amazing, alot of different modes, the fans are quiet even on highest speed, it keeps everything really cool. You won't regret buying these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value but with some limitations
reviews.reviewText: These were better that expected for their cost. Only issue I had is that one of the fans makes a slightly noticeable clicking noise at the highest speed but at medium they are fine. If I had paid more I would have returned but the time to remove them all and replace isn’t worth the effort. Wish I could replace just the one.Update: I decide to reach out to the seller regarding the one fan that was making a clicking sound. All I can say is their customer service is outstanding and they resolved my issue! They get an grade of A+!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Bright White is all they do. New one arrives, with a remote, a remote which was absent in 1st order
reviews.reviewText: setup was seemingly easy. its all light weight plastic stuff and the fans will only work in line with their small flimsy controller. a controller which offers no control. The fans stay bright white and spin full blast. If there was once a control on it, I might be able to switch modes, as the advertisement promised, but no , just a hole in the which states "key". But no key. Just a hole. No sweat was going to hook it to mystic on the MB or so a sane man would think... Yet that only worked for 36 hours and the fans turned bright white. To send them back, my machine is down. So what am I to do? Is bright white and full blast my future?I got a replacement today. LO and Behold, upon opening the box, there was a remote control. This was not in the 1st box sent. It makes a world of difference.
